# <type>(<scope>): <subject>   — ≤50 chars, imperative ("add", not "added")
#
# <body> — wrap at 72 chars. Explain *what* and *why*, not *how*.
#
# <footer> — e.g. "Closes #123", "BREAKING CHANGE: ..."
#
# Conventional Commit types:
#   feat     A new feature
#   fix      A bug fix
#   docs     Documentation only
#   style    Formatting; no code-behavior change
#   refactor Neither a fix nor a feature
#   perf     A performance improvement
#   test     Adding or fixing tests
#   build    Build system or dependencies
#   ci       CI configuration
#   chore    Other changes that don't touch src or tests
#
# Enable this template once with:
#   git config commit.template .gitmessage
